<section>
  <h2>Design Philosophy</h2>
  <p>VB classes are <strong>element-scoped</strong>, not generic utilities. <code>.compact</code> on a <code>&lt;table&gt;</code> reduces cell padding. <code>.compact</code> on a <code>&lt;header&gt;</code> reduces header padding. Same word, appropriate behavior for each context.</p>
  <p>This means you can read the HTML and understand the intent: <code>&lt;nav class="pills"&gt;</code> is a pill navigation. No need to decode a chain of utility classes.</p>
</section>
